{"body":"[{\"data\":1,\"prerenderedAt\":189},[\"ShallowReactive\",2],{\"blog-en\":3},[4],{\"id\":5,\"title\":6,\"body\":7,\"date\":173,\"description\":174,\"draft\":175,\"extension\":176,\"meta\":177,\"navigation\":178,\"path\":179,\"readingTime\":180,\"seo\":181,\"stem\":182,\"tags\":183,\"__hash__\":188},\"blog_en\\u002Fen\\u002Fblog\\u002Fresilient-microservices.md\",\"Building Resilient Microservices: Lessons from Banking at Scale\",{\"type\":8,\"value\":9,\"toc\":165},\"minimark\",[10,15,19,24,27,74,77,81,84,98,101,105,108,126,129,133,136,162],[11,12,14],\"h1\",{\"id\":13},\"building-resilient-microservices\",\"Building Resilient Microservices\",[16,17,18],\"p\",{},\"After modernizing two major banking platforms, I've learned that the hardest part isn't the technology — it's the organizational and data boundaries.\",[20,21,23],\"h2\",{\"id\":22},\"start-with-bounded-contexts\",\"Start with Bounded Contexts\",[16,25,26],{},\"The biggest mistake teams make is splitting by technical layer (controller\\u002Fservice\\u002Frepository) instead of business domain. When we decomposed Banco Nacional's monolith, we identified 7 bounded contexts first:\",[28,29,30,38,44,50,56,62,68],\"ul\",{},[31,32,33,37],\"li\",{},[34,35,36],\"strong\",{},\"Accounts\",\" — balance, account history\",[31,39,40,43],{},[34,41,42],{},\"Transfers\",\" — internal and external transfers\",[31,45,46,49],{},[34,47,48],{},\"Payments\",\" — bill pay, scheduled payments\",[31,51,52,55],{},[34,53,54],{},\"Auth\",\" — session, OAuth, 2FA\",[31,57,58,61],{},[34,59,60],{},\"Notifications\",\" — push, SMS, email\",[31,63,64,67],{},[34,65,66],{},\"Audit\",\" — regulatory logging\",[31,69,70,73],{},[34,71,72],{},\"Reconciliation\",\" — end-of-day settlement\",[16,75,76],{},\"Each became a microservice. Each owned its database. No shared tables.\",[20,78,80],{\"id\":79},\"polyglot-persistence-is-real\",\"Polyglot Persistence Is Real\",[16,82,83],{},\"Not every service needs PostgreSQL. We used:\",[28,85,86,89,92,95],{},[31,87,88],{},\"PostgreSQL for ACID-required flows (transfers, payments)\",[31,90,91],{},\"Redis for session state and rate limiting\",[31,93,94],{},\"MongoDB for audit logs (write-heavy, schema-flexible)\",[31,96,97],{},\"Kafka as the event backbone\",[16,99,100],{},\"This reduced cost and improved fit-for-purpose. But it introduced operational complexity — you need observability tooling that works across data stores.\",[20,102,104],{\"id\":103},\"deployment-strategy-matters-more-than-you-think\",\"Deployment Strategy Matters More Than You Think\",[16,106,107],{},\"Blue-green deployments saved us more than once. The pattern:\",[109,110,111,114,117,120,123],\"ol\",{},[31,112,113],{},\"Deploy new version to green environment (0% traffic)\",[31,115,116],{},\"Run smoke tests against green\",[31,118,119],{},\"Shift 10% traffic to green (canary)\",[31,121,122],{},\"Monitor error rate for 5 minutes\",[31,124,125],{},\"Shift 100% or rollback — decision in \\u003C 10 minutes\",[16,127,128],{},\"This is impossible with a monolith. With microservices, it's routine.\",[20,130,132],{\"id\":131},\"the-real-cost-of-microservices\",\"The Real Cost of Microservices\",[16,134,135],{},\"Microservices aren't free. You pay in:\",[28,137,138,144,150,156],{},[31,139,140,143],{},[34,141,142],{},\"Operational complexity\",\" — distributed tracing, service mesh, log aggregation\",[31,145,146,149],{},[34,147,148],{},\"Network latency\",\" — every cross-service call adds 5-20ms\",[31,151,152,155],{},[34,153,154],{},\"Eventual consistency\",\" — you can't do a JOIN across services\",[31,157,158,161],{},[34,159,160],{},\"Testing\",\" — contract tests, integration tests, end-to-end tests\",[16,163,164],{},\"The payoff: independent deployment, independent scaling, fault isolation. For banking at scale, the trade-off is worth it.\",{\"title\":166,\"searchDepth\":167,\"depth\":167,\"links\":168},\"\",2,[169,170,171,172],{\"id\":22,\"depth\":167,\"text\":23},{\"id\":79,\"depth\":167,\"text\":80},{\"id\":103,\"depth\":167,\"text\":104},{\"id\":131,\"depth\":167,\"text\":132},\"2024-12-15\",\"What I learned modernizing banking platforms — from monolith to 40+ microservices handling 12M requests\\u002Fday.\",false,\"md\",{},true,\"\\u002Fen\\u002Fblog\\u002Fresilient-microservices\",8,{\"title\":6,\"description\":174},\"en\\u002Fblog\\u002Fresilient-microservices\",[184,185,186,187],\"microservices\",\"banking\",\"architecture\",\"kubernetes\",\"lu7zm10mHWYTOUct3pM90yxzp2lKOsCc6lWfUJGLh4M\",1783828259331]","statusCode":200,"statusMessage":"","headers":{"content-type":"application/json;charset=utf-8","x-powered-by":"Nuxt"}}